 1) SWEET POTATO CRISPSLay thinly sliced sweet potatoes, without overlapping, on a microwave-safe plate lined with baking paper. Sprinkle with a little water, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and rosemary. Microwave on high for 5 minutes. Cool before storing in an airtight container. 2) CHOCOLATE CAKE IN A MUGMix cup cake flour, cup sugar and 3 tbsp cocoa powder in a 300ml mug. Stir in 1 large egg, 3 tbsp milk, 3 tbsp oil and 1 tsp vanilla extract. Microwave on high for 3 minutes. Cool slightly and serve with cream or custard.Yes, you really can cook a gourmet breakfast in the microwave 3) ROASTED GARLICPlace 2 whole garlic bulbs in a oven bag and sprinkle with salt and olive oil. Microwave on high for 6 minutes. Cool in the bag for 10 minutes before squeezing out the soft garlic from each clove. Spread on toast, a baked potato or vegetables. 4) POPPADOMSWorking with 2-3 poppadoms at a time, lightly brush both sides with oil. Pile on a paper towel or bake paper and microwave for 2 minutes till puffed up. 5) DRIED TOMATOESWash and dry firm red tomatoes and slice in half lengthways. Scoop out seeds and liquid and dry with paper towel. Place cut side up on a microwave-safe cooking rack, ensuring they don t touch. Sprinkle with salt and microwave on low for 45 minutes, turning frequently, until dried. Cooking time depends on wattage. Cool completely and pack in sealable plastic bags. 6) CARAMELISED POPCORNCombine 1 cup brown sugar, cup butter, 4 tbsp syrup and pinch of salt in glass bowl and microwave on high for 2 minutes. Stir, then cook for 2 more minutes. Stir in tsp bicarb and pour hot syrup over popped popcorn in a brown paper bag. Shake well and cook on high for 1-2 minutes. Shake bag, then cook for another 2 minutes; shake and cook for 1 minute more.